{{Quote|Celebration is basically Woodstock for ''Star Wars'' fans.|Jason Crawford|<ref name="Quote">{{SWArchive|url=community/news/rocks/f20070508/indexp2.html|text=Grey Does Matter: C4 Dreaming}}</ref>}}
'''Celebration''' is a series of ''Star Wars'' fan conventions sponsored by [[Lucasfilm]] ''Star Wars'' Celebrations have been held every few years since [[1999]].

===[[Celebration (1999)|Celebration]]===
Celebration was held prior to the release of [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''The Phantom Menace'']] in [[1999]]. The convention was held in [[Wikipedia:Denver, Colorado|Denver, Colorado]].

===[[Celebration II]]===
Celebration II was held prior to the release of [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']] in [[2002]]. It ran from [[May 3]] to [[May 5]] [[2002]], in [[Wikipedia:Indianapolis, Indiana|Indianapolis, Indiana]].

===[[Celebration III]]===
Celebration III was held to celebrate the release of [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Revenge of the Sith'']]. It ran from [[April 21]] to [[April 24]] [[2005]], in Indianapolis, Indiana.

===[[Celebration IV]]===
Celebration IV was held to celebrate 30 years of [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'']]. It was held from [[May 24]] to [[May 28]], [[2007]], in [[Wikipedia:Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles, California]].

===[[Celebration Europe (2007)|Celebration Europe]]===
Celebration Europe was held in [[Wikipedia:London|London, United Kingdom]] to celebrate 30 years of ''Star Wars''. It was the first Celebration to be held outside the United States. It ran from [[July 13]] to [[July 15]], [[2007]].

===[[Celebration Japan (2008)|Celebration Japan]]===
Celebration Japan was held at the [[Wikipedia:Makuhari Messe|Makuhari-Messe Convention Center]] near [[Wikipedia:Tokyo|Tokyo]] from [[July 19]] to [[July 21]], [[2008]]. It was the first Celebration to be held in Japan. Its purpose was to celebrate the 30th anniversary of ''A New Hope'', the original ''Star Wars'' film, which debuted in Japan on June 24, 1978.

===[[Celebration V]]===
Celebration V was held from [[August 12]] to [[August 15]], [[2010]], in [[Wikipedia:Orlando, Florida|Orlando, Florida]], to celebrate 30 years of [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']].<ref>{{SWArchive|url=fans/events/c5announcement/index.html|text=Lucasfilm and Reed Exhibitions are Proud to Announce ''Star Wars'' Celebration V}}</ref>

===[[Celebration VI]]===
Celebration VI was held from [[August 23]] to [[August 26]], [[2012]], and returned to Orlando, Florida.

===[[Celebration Europe II]]===
Celebration Europe II was held from [[July 26]] to [[July 28]], [[2013]], and for the first time held in Essen, Germany.

===[[Celebration Anaheim (2015)|Celebration Anaheim]]===
Celebration Anaheim was held in Anaheim, California from [[April 16]] to [[April 19]], [[2015]], coinciding with the theatrical release of the second trailer for [[Star Wars: Episode VII The Force Awakens|Episode VII ''The Force Awakens'']].

===[[Celebration Europe (2016)]]===
[[File:Carrie-and-Gary-Fishers.png|thumb|right|300px|[[Carrie Fisher]] and her pet dog Gary at Celebration 2016]]
Celebration London was held in London, United Kingdom, [[July 15]] through [[July 17]], [[2016]].

===[[Celebration Orlando]]===
On [[May 4]], 2016, Lucasfilm announced Celebration 2017, which took place in Orlando, Florida, from [[April 13]] through [[April 16]], 2017.

===[[Celebration Chicago]]===
On [[March 8]], 2017, Lucasfilm announced Celebration 2019, which took place in Chicago, Illinois, from [[April 11]] through [[April 15]], 2019.

===[[Celebration Anaheim (2022)]]===
On April 15, 2019, Lucasfilm announced Celebration 2020, which would have taken place once again in Anaheim, California, in [[2020]],<ref name="Celebration 2019">{{StarWarsShow|sP6SaKn2WuM|Star Wars Celebration Chicago 2019 Live Stream - Day 4 &#124; The Star Wars Show LIVE!}}</ref> but was cancelled due to the ongoing [[Wikipedia:COVID-19 pandemic|COVID-19 pandemic]] and rescheduled for the same location in August [[2022]].<ref name="Postponement">{{SW|url=news/an-update-on-star-wars-celebration-2020|text=An Update on ''Star Wars'' Celebration 2020}}</ref><ref>{{WebCite|url=https://deadline.com/2020/06/star-wars-celebration-canceled-will-return-2022-1202959943|text=Star Wars Celebration Canceled, Set To Return In 2022|author=Ramos, Dino-Ray|date=2020-06-16|archivedate=20200616042022}}</ref><ref>{{WebCite|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/star-wars-celebration-2020-canceled-coroanvirus-1234635590|text=Star Wars Celebration Canceled for First Time, Sets New Date for 2022|author=Murphy, J. Kim|date=2020-06-15|archivedate=20200616065020}}</ref> The 2020 art show did continue via the internet, however.<ref name="Celebration 2020 Art">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-celebration-2020-art-show-revealed-exclusive|text=''Star Wars'' Celebration 2020 Art Show Revealed &ndash; Exclusive}}</ref> On [[May 12]], [[2021]], [[StarWars.com]] announced that the Celebration was being moved up from August, and would now be held from [[May 26]] to [[May 29]], 2022.<ref name="Preponement">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-celebration-anaheim-2022-dates-changing|text=''Star Wars'' Celebration Anaheim 2022 Dates Changing}}</ref>

===[[Celebration Europe (2023)]]===
On May 29, 2022, Lucasfilm announced Celebration 2023, which took place in London, United Kingdom, [[April 7]] through [[April 10]], [[2023]].<ref name="Twitter Announcement">{{Twitter|starwars|status/1531047358141587456|[[Star Wars]]|quote=Let's do it again next year. #StarWarsCelebration returns to Europe in 2023.|archivedate=20220530055619}}</ref>

===[[Celebration Japan (2025)]]===
On [[February 21]], 2023, StarWars.com revealed a celebration would take place in [[2025]].<ref name="Celebration 2025">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-celebration-reasons-to-go|text=5 Reasons to Go to ''Star Wars'' Celebration for the First Time}}</ref> It was later revealed to be in Japan, and ran [[April 18]] through [[April 20]].<ref name="SW.com Japan">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-celebration-japan-2025|text=''Star Wars'' Celebration Heads to Japan in 2025}}</ref>

===[[Celebration Los Angeles]]===
On April 20, Lucasfilm announced a celebration would be held in Los Angeles from [[April 1]] to [[April 4]], [[2027]].<ref name="Celebration 2027">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-celebration-2027|text=''Star Wars'' Celebration Visits Los Angeles in 2027}}</ref>

==An Online Revelry: May the 4th Be With You and Revenge of the 5th==
On May 4 and 5, 2020, the organization that sponsors Celebrations hosted an online showcase of ''Star Wars'' events due to the COVID-19 pandemic.<ref>{{WebCite|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/virtual-star-wars-convention-launch-may-4th-1292521|text=Virtual 'Star Wars' Convention to Launch for May the 4th|author=McMillan, Graeme|date=2020-04-29|work=The Hollywood Reporter|archivedate=20200504101228}}</ref>

